<Seo Canonical="/docs/extensions/datagrid/selection/custom-row-colors" Title="Blazorise DataGrid Custom Row Colors" Description="Learn Blazorise by the example. Easily color code your data with the Blazorise DataGrid's custom row color feature." />

<DocsPageTitle Path="Extensions/DataGrid/Selection/Custom Row Colors">
    Blazorise DataGrid: Custom Row Colors
</DocsPageTitle>

<DocsPageLead>
    Control the look and feel of each row.
</DocsPageLead>

<DocsPageSubtitle>
    Overview
</DocsPageSubtitle>

<DocsPageParagraph>
    You have full control over appearance of each row, including the selected rows.
</DocsPageParagraph>

<Alert Color="Color.Info" Visible>
    <Paragraph Margin="Margin.Is0.FromBottom">
        <Code>RowStyling</Code> and <Code>SelectedRowStyling</Code> are applied to the table row element. Some CSS frameworks, especially Bootstrap table styles, can also style table cells directly and override row-level text or background styles.
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Margin="Margin.Is0.FromBottom">
        If you need the styling to apply reliably to the full rendered row, prefer <Code>CellStyling</Code> and <Code>SelectedCellStyling</Code>, or assign a custom class and target the row cells with a selector like <Code>tr.my-row &gt; td</Code>.
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Margin="Margin.Is0.FromBottom">
        As a last resort, you can also use an explicit <Code>!important</Code> in your custom CSS or style string.
    </Paragraph>
</Alert>

<DocsPageParagraph>
    The example below uses cell styling so the row colors remain consistent across providers.
</DocsPageParagraph>

